{"id":"omer","term":"Omer","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A handful, one-tenth of an ephah=half a gallon dry measure (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 16:22\">Ex. 16:22</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 16:32\">32</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 16:33\">33</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 16:36\">36</a>)=“tenth deal.”</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 16:22","Exodus 16:32","Exodus 16:33","Exodus 16:36"]}